Definition: change to the contrary
Example: The trend was reversed; the tides turned against him; public opinion turned when it was revealed that the president had an affair with a White House intern
Synonyms: turn, noun, event, verb, contact, turn_on, turn_off, reverse, adj, all, revocable, reversible, relation, act, reversal, change, to, the, contrary, The, trend, was, reversed, tides, turned, against, him, public, opinion, when, it, revealed, that, president, had, an, affair, with, a, White, House, intern
Frame: 1,2,8,10,11
Category: verb.change
